Functions can allow input.
Parameter is the assigned variable to the actual data whereas the argument is the actual data,
(eg.
someone = "Anri"  --> Parameter is someone and argument is "Anri."
greet(someone)
)

POSITIONAL AND KEYWORD FUNCTIONS
Positional:
    def greet(name, location):
        ...

    greet("anri", "cape town")

Keyword:
    def greet(name, location)
        ...

    greet(location="cape town", name="anri")